-- Ukraine’s Sovereign Debt Fell 1.1% in May, Finance Ministry Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-06-25T14:29:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/ukraine-s-sovereign-debt-fell-1-1-in-may-finance-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s state debt, including
guarantees, declined 1.1 percent last month as the central bank
repaid part of a loan from the International Monetary Fund.  Debt fell to $60.25 billion as of May 31 from $60.9 billion
a month earlier, the  Finance Ministry , based in the capital,
Kiev, said today in a  statement  on its website.  Domestic debt grew to $22.78 billion from $22.34 billion,
while foreign debt fell to $24.19 billion from $24.53 billion,
it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
